description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Falls Prevention Service Team Leader within Wye Valley NHS Trust with clinical hours as a Physiotherapist.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a fixed term post of 25 hours per week is for 12-14 months. An internal secondment will also be considered. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be responsible for their own clinical caseload (multifactorial falls risk assessment and interventions in a clinic setting) and the strategic planning and daily running of this service. You will need to be forward thinking, innovative and have excellent communication and organisational skills. You will require an ability to work flexibly, exploring ideas, and adapting practices to deliver a more efficient service in line with local and national drivers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder should have significant falls prevention experience as well as relevant management experience and be committed to providing high quality evidence based practice and patient experience. Vestibular experience would be desirable. You will be responsible for the management of a mixture of Physiotherapy, Occupational Therapy, Support Staff and administrative staff.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will play an active part of an on-going in-service training, student education and clinical supervision providing leadership, expert supervision and teaching to colleagues in order to support your own professional development and others.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please contact Jo Burns on 07970 217742 or by email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;joanne.burns@wvt.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; for an informal visit or more information.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
